FBIS3-33108 "drlat034_b_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-034 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Feb 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti PANPRA `Leanings' Precipitate Leader Resignations FL1702215894 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 GMT 17 Feb 94 FL1702215894 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] Agronomist Roosevelt (Saindic) officially announced his resignation from PANPRA [National Progressive Revolutionary Party of Haiti] leadership after having discontinued participation in their activities as of May 1993. The resignation letter of Roosevelt (Saindic) mentions deep opposition to his management style from several members of the party, especially concerning work methods, strategy, and the party's current political leanings. The resignation of (Saindic) from PANPRA's leadership, follows that of several other members of this political party including Georges Weirleigh, Arnold Antonin, and Claude Elisma.
